07/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic said Monday (6 October) that while there would be no government reshuffle, he expects changes within the ministries as a result of a new programme. The government recently adopted 12 measures aimed at streamlining its work. The cabinet's first task is to examine the work of all units in the ministries and to identify problem areas. (BBC, Tanjug, Beta, B92 - 06/10/03)
